obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (103407)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103407&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Sports Governance`
  line `Act, 2025.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint, and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act, and`
  line `any reference in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to`
  line `the coming into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 31st day of December, 2025--- Ss.1 to 3, sub-sections (1), (2) and (4) of section 4, sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 5,`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 8, sub-section (1) of section 11, section 14, section 15, sub-sections (1) to (7) and (10) of section 17,`
  line `section 30, section 31, section 33 to 38, vide notification no. S.O. 6152 (E), dated 1st January, 2026, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, s. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (103408)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103408&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(a) "ad hoc administrative body" means a body constituted for ad hoc administration under`
  line `section 11;`
  line
  line `(b) "affiliate unit" means the State, district or other units of,---`
  line
  line `(i) the National Olympic Committee;`
  line
  line `(ii) the National Paralympic Committee;`
  line
  line `(iii) the National Sports Federation; and`
  line
  line `(iv) the Regional Sports Federation;`
  line
  line `(c) "Athletes Committee", "Disputes Resolution Committee", "Ethics Committee" and "Executive`
  line `Committee", by whatever name called, means the "Athletes Committee", "Disputes Resolution Committee", "Ethics Committee" and "Executive Committee", respectively, of a National Sports`
  line Body;
  line
  line `(d) "Board" means the National Sports Board established under sub-section (1) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(e) "Board recognition" means recognition of a sports organisation by the Board under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "bye-laws" means the memorandum of association or articles of association, by whatever name`
  line `called, of a sports organisation;`
  line
  line `(g) "designated sport" means any sport discipline as may be specified by the Central Government,`
  line `by notification, to be a designated sport for a specific region or State or for the whole of India;`
  line
  line `(h) "International Charters and Statutes" means the Olympic Charter and other Charters and`
  line `Statutes of the international sports governing bodies and include any bye-laws, rules, regulations or`
  line `constitution, by whatever name called, as may be adopted, amended or issued by such bodies from`
  line `time to time;`
  line
  line `(i) "International Federation" means---`
  line
  line `(A) a federation recognised as such by the International Olympic Committee in respect of an`
  line `Olympic sport; or`
  line
  line `(B) a federation recognised as such by the International Paralympic Committee in respect of a`
  line `Paralympic sport; or`
  line
  line `(C) a federation which regulates the sport at international level in respect of non-Olympic or`
  line `non-Paralympic sports;`
  line
  line `(j) "International Olympic Committee" means the governing body for the Olympic Games;`
  line
  line `(k) "International Paralympic Committee" means the governing body for the Paralympic Games;`
  line
  line `(l) "international recognition" means the recognition of a national sports governing body by the`
  line `concerned international sports governing body;`
  line
  line `(m) "International Sports Body" means an international sports governing body such as the`
  line `International Olympic Committee or the International Paralympic Committee or International`
  line `Federation or a continental governing body for sports;`
  line
  line `(n) "National Olympic Committee" means the National Olympic Committee established under`
  line `section 3 as a national sports governing body and recognised as the National Olympic Committee of`
  line `India by the International Olympic Committee;`
  line
  line `(o) "National Paralympic Committee" means the National Paralympic Committee established under`
  line `section 3 as a national sports governing body and recognised as the National Paralympic Committee of`
  line `India by the International Paralympic Committee;`
  line
  line `(p) "National Sports Body" means a national sports governing body such as the National Olympic`
  line `Committee or the National Paralympic Committee or the National Sports Federation or the Regional`
  line `Sports Federation, established under section 3;`
  line
  line `(q) "National Sports Election Panel" means the National Sports Election Panel notified under`
  line `section 16 to oversee the conduct of free and fair elections to the Executive Committee and the`
  line `Athletes Committee of the National Sports Bodies;`
  line
  line `(r) "National Sports Federation" means a National Sports Federation established under section 3 as`
  line `a national sports governing body for a designated sport;`
  line
  line `(s) "National Sports Promotion Organisation" means a sports organisation or body contributing`
  line `towards the development of sports, such as talent identification and their nurturing, policy advocacy`
  line `relating to sports administration or welfare and recognised by the Board under sub-section (7) of`
  line `section 8;`
  line
  line `(t) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the expression "notify"`
  line `or "notified", shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(u) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made by the Central Government under this Act;`
  line
  line `(v) "recognised sports organisation" means a sports organisation recognised by the Board as a`
  line `National Sports Body under sub-section (1) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(w) "Regional Sports Federation" means a Regional Sports Federation established under section 3`
  line `as national sports governing body for a designated sport;`
  line
  line `(x) "regulations" means regulations made by the Board under this Act;`
  line
  line `(y) "Secretary General" means the Secretary General or the Secretary of a National Sports Body;`
  line
  line `(z) "sportsperson of outstanding merit" means a sportsperson referred to in the proviso to clause (a)`
  line `of sub-section (1) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(za) "State" means a State specified in the First Schedule to the Constitution and includes a Union`
  line territory;
  line
  line `(zb) "Tribunal" means the National Sports Tribunal constituted under sub-section (1) of section 17.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (103409)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of national sports governing bodies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103409&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following bodies shall be`
  line `established as the national sports governing bodies for their respective recognised sports organisations,`
  line `namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the National Olympic Committee;`
  line
  line `(b) the National Paralympic Committee;`
  line
  line `(c) a National Sports Federation for each designated sport; and`
  line
  line `(d) a Regional Sports Federation for each designated sport.`
  line
  line `(2) There shall be only one National Olympic Committee and one National Paralympic Committee,`
  line `each governing multi-sport disciplines.`
  line
  line `(3) The National Olympic Committee shall have an international recognition and affiliation of the`
  line `International Olympic Committee.`
  line
  line `(4) The National Paralympic Committee shall have an international recognition and affiliation of the`
  line `International Paralympic Committee.`
  line
  line `(5) Every National Sports Federation shall have an international recognition and affiliation of the`
  line `concerned international sports governing body:`
  line
  line `Provided that this sub-section shall not apply to a designated sport which does not have an`
  line `international sports governing body.`
  line
  line `(6) Every Regional Sports Federation shall have the relevant affiliations as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (103410)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Compliance with certain requirements by National Sports Bodies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103410&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every National Sports`
  line `Body shall have,---`
  line
  line `(a) a General Body, consisting of equal number of representatives from each of its affiliate units`
  line `and such other ex officio members as per its bye-laws and the International Charters and Statutes, as`
  line `applicable:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall have representation of such sportspersons of outstanding merit and such other`
  line `categories of persons, as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) an Executive Committee which shall consist of not more than fifteen members, of whom---`
  line
  line `(i) at least two shall be sportspersons of outstanding merit;`
  line
  line `(ii) two shall be from the Athletes Committee to be elected from amongst themselves; and`
  line
  line `(iii) such number of ex officio and other members shall be nominated or elected, as the case may`
  line `be, as per the International Charters and Statutes and the bye-laws:`
  line
  line `Provided that at least four members shall be women:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the voting rights of elected representatives of the Athletes Committee in the`
  line `Executive Committee shall be as determined by the bye-laws;`
  line
  line `(c) an Ethics Committee to be constituted as per its bye-laws and the International Charters and`
  line `Statutes, as applicable:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Ethics Committee of the National Olympic Committee shall function as the`
  line `Ethics Committee of any National Sports Body which does not have such Committee;`
  line
  line `(d) a Dispute Resolution Committee to be constituted as per its bye-laws and the International`
  line `Charters and Statutes, as applicable:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Dispute Resolution Committee of the National Olympic Committee shall function`
  line `as the Dispute Resolution Committee of any National Sports Body which does not have such`
  line Committee;
  line
  line `(e) an Athletes Committee consisting of elected members as determined by the bye-laws;`
  line
  line `(f) a President who shall be the head of the concerned National Sports Body and shall preside over`
  line `the meetings of its Executive Committee and the General Body;`
  line
  line `(g) a Secretary General who shall be the head of administration responsible for carrying out all`
  line `decisions of the Executive Committee and the General Body:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the International Charters and Statutes provide for a full-time head of`
  line `administration, by whatever name called, there shall not be an elected post of the head of`
  line administration;
  line
  line `(h) a Treasurer who shall be the custodian of funds or the accounts of the concerned National`
  line `Sports Body.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not be qualified to contest for election or seek nomination to, the Executive`
  line `Committee, unless---`
  line
  line `(a) such person is a citizen of India who has attained at least twenty-five years of age;`
  line
  line `(b) the nomination of such person is duly proposed and seconded by a voting member of the`
  line `General Body;`
  line
  line `(c) such person is not declared to be of unsound mind;`
  line
  line `(d) such person complies with the International Charters and Statutes and bye-laws relating to age`
  line `and term of the Executive Committee:`
  line
  line `Provided that such person shall not be more than seventy years of age on the last date of`
  line `nomination for election:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any person, aged between seventy and seventy-five years, may contest`
  line `elections or seek nominations, if permitted by the International Charters and Statutes and the bye-laws`
  line `and in case such person is elected, he shall serve for a full term;`
  line
  line `(e) such person, if he is a government servant, has necessary approvals from the Government, as`
  line `applicable:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person shall not be qualified to contest for election or seek nomination to, the posts`
  line `of the President or the Secretary General or the Treasurer, unless such person is a sportsperson of`
  line `outstanding merit or, has previously served as a member for at least one full term in the Executive`
  line `Committee of the National Sports Body or as the President, or the Secretary General or the Treasurer`
  line `in its affiliate unit:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a person may continuously hold the position of either the President or the`
  line `Secretary General or the Treasurer, as the case may be, for up to three consecutive terms separately, or in`
  line `combination thereof and shall be eligible for election to such posts or to the Executive Committee after a`
  line `mandatory cooling off period of one term.`
  line
  line `(3) The term of the Executive Committee shall be as provided in the bye-laws subject to a maximum`
  line `period of four years.`
  line
  line `(4) The mode of election to different bodies, committees and offices including their term, eligibility`
  line `criteria and disqualification of members thereof, and other matters of governance shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (103411)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Establishment of National Sports Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103411&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification,`
  line `establish a Board to be known as the National Sports Board, consisting of a Chairperson and such number`
  line `of other Members as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson and the Members referred to in sub-section (1) shall be appointed by the Central`
  line `Government from amongst persons of ability, integrity and standing who possesses special knowledge or`
  line `practical experience in the field of public administration, sports governance, sports law and other related`
  line `fields, on the recommendation of a search-cum-selection committee comprising of such number of`
  line `persons, having wide experience in public administration, sports administration and recipients of national`
  line `sports awards, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The salary and allowances and the term of office of the Chairperson and other Members of the`
  line `Board and other terms and conditions of their service, including removal from service, shall be such as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal, with power subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property,`
  line `both movable and immovable, and to contract, and shall, by the said name, sue or be sued.`
  line
  line `(5) The head office of the Board shall be at Delhi and the Board shall establish its branch offices at`
  line `such other places as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (103412)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Powers and functions of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103412&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall exercise and perform the following powers and`
  line `functions to carry out the provisions of this Act, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the grant of Board recognition to sports organisations and registration of affiliate units and to`
  line `suspend or cancel such recognition or registration;`
  line
  line `(b) to maintain a register of the National Sports Bodies and each of their respective affiliate units in`
  line `such manner as may be specified by regulations;`
  line
  line `(c) to conduct inquiries on matters specified in section 9;`
  line
  line `(d) to constitute an ad hoc administrative body or to direct the concerned National Sports Body or`
  line `their affiliate units, as the case may be, to so constitute, as per section 11;`
  line
  line `(e) to issue guidelines for formulation of the Code of Ethics by the National Sports Bodies;`
  line
  line `(f) to frame Safe Sports Policy for the protection and safety of women, minor athletes and other`
  line `classes of persons;`
  line
  line `(g) maintain a roster of the National Sports Election Panel as per section 16;`
  line
  line `(h) collaborate with the International Sports Bodies and National Sports Bodies for the`
  line `development of sports and welfare of athletes in India and to issue guidelines to the National Sports`
  line `Bodies for ensuring compliance with the international standards and best practices of the Olympic and`
  line `sports movement;`
  line
  line `(i) take such measures as may be prescribed, to ensure the protection of the rights and welfare of`
  line `athletes and support personnel; and`
  line
  line `(j) such other powers and functions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (103413)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Staff of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103413&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, in consultation with the Board, appoint such`
  line `officers and other employees as may be necessary for discharging the functions of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The officers and other employees of the Board shall discharge their functions under the general`
  line `superintendence and control of the Chairperson or any other member of the Board to whom powers for`
  line `exercising such superintendence and control are delegated by the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(3) The qualifications, appointment, salary and allowances and other terms and conditions of service`
  line `of the officers and other employees of the Board shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (103414)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Board recognition and registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103414&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall have the power to grant Board`
  line `recognition to any sports organisation as a National Sports Body.`
  line
  line `(2) Any sports organisation desirous of obtaining Board recognition as a National Sports Body under`
  line `this section shall apply to the Board in such form and manner and containing such particulars, as may be`
  line `specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) No sports organisation shall be recognised under sub-section (1) unless such organisation,---`
  line
  line `(a) is a society registered under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860) or under the`
  line `Societies Registration Act of a State; or`
  line
  line `(b) is a not-for-profit company incorporated under section 8 of the Companies Act, 2013`
  line `(18 of 2013); or`
  line
  line `(c) is a trust created under the Indian Trusts Act, 1882 (2 of 1882) or under the Trusts Act of a`
  line `State; and`
  line
  line `(d) complies with such other criteria and conditions as may be specified by regulations and having`
  line `the sole object of the development of sports.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board recognition granted under this section shall be renewed periodically at such intervals`
  line `and in accordance with such procedure as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(5) All sports organisations recognised as National Sports Bodies by the Central Government before`
  line `the commencement of this Act, shall be deemed to have Board recognition under this Act and the`
  line `provisions of this Act shall, mutatis mutandis, apply to such organisation.`
  line
  line `(6) All affiliate units of National Sports Bodies shall ensure that they are registered with the Board,`
  line `subject to such conditions and in such manner, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) The Board, subject to the prior approval of the Central Government, shall also have the power to`
  line `recognise sports organisations participating in sports governance, athlete support and welfare, as National`
  line `Sports Promotion Organisation.`
  line
  line `(8) The eligibility criteria for Board recognition and the manner of governance and functioning of the`
  line `National Sports Promotion Organisations shall be such as may be specified by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that a National Sports Promotion Organisation recognised by the Central Government before`
  line `the commencement of this Act, shall be deemed to have been recognised as such under this Act and the`
  line `provisions of this Act shall, mutatis mutandis, apply to such organisation:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Board recognition granted under this sub-section shall be renewed`
  line `periodically at such intervals and in accordance with such procedure as may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (103415)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power of Board to conduct inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103415&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, either on its own motion, or in response to`
  line `complaint received from any person or body on matters affecting the welfare of sportspersons or the`
  line `development of sports in the country or misuse of public funds, conduct an inquiry where it is satisfied`
  line `that there is a reasonable cause so to do:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such complaint shall be entertained unless the complainant has exhausted all`
  line `available remedies with the National Sports Body or its affiliate units:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Board may entertain such complaint if it is satisfied that accessing those`
  line `remedies would result in unnecessary delay or unreasonable prejudice.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (103416)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Power of Board to suspend or cancel Board recognition or registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103416&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may,`
  line `either on its own motion, or on the receipt of a complaint by an aggrieved party, by order, suspend or`
  line `cancel the Board recognition of a sports organisation as a National Sports Body or registration of an`
  line `affiliate unit of a National Sports Body, in any of the following circumstances, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the international recognition of the concerned National Sports Body has been suspended or`
  line `cancelled by the concerned International Sports Body;`
  line
  line `(b) the concerned affiliate unit has been suspended or disaffiliated by the concerned National`
  line `Sports Body;`
  line
  line `(c) the National Sports Body has violated any of the provisions of this Act or the rules or`
  line `regulations made thereunder, including eligibility criteria or terms and conditions of the Board`
  line recognition;
  line
  line `(d) the Registrar of Companies or the Registrar of Societies of the concerned sports organisation`
  line `has reported gross irregularities in the internal functioning or removed the name of the National Sports`
  line `Body or its affiliate units;`
  line
  line `(e) the National Sports Body or the affiliate unit has---`
  line
  line `(i) failed to hold elections for its Executive Committee or has committed gross irregularities in`
  line `the election procedures thereof; or`
  line
  line `(ii) failed to publish its annual audited accounts; or`
  line
  line `(iii) has misused, misapplied or misappropriated any public funds:`
  line
  line `Provided that the suspension or disaffiliation referred to in clause (a) and clause (b) shall be`
  line `co-terminus with the suspension or disaffiliation by the concerned International Sports Body or the`
  line `National Sports Body, as the case may be, which may be extended by the Board, for reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing, for such further period as the Board may consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) Before issuing an order of suspension or cancellation of Board recognition or registration under`
  line `sub-section (1), the Board shall consult the concerned---`
  line
  line `(a) International Sports Body, where such suspension or cancellation of Board recognition concerns`
  line `the National Sports Federation or the Regional Sports Federation;`
  line
  line `(b) National Sports Federation or the Regional Sports Federation, where such suspension or`
  line `cancellation of registration concerns any affiliate unit,`
  line
  line `and upon such consultation, take any of the following measures, namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) issue an order, directing the National Sports Body or its affiliate unit, to take such action as is`
  line `appropriate to correct the deficiency and upon compliance, the Board may make a finding of`
  line `compliance; or`
  line
  line `(ii) conduct a hearing by giving reasonable opportunity to the parties to present their case before`
  line `pronouncing its decision.`
  line
  line `(3) An appeal against any order of the Board for suspension or cancellation of Board recognition or`
  line `registration under this section shall lie with the Tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (103417)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Ad hoc administrative body.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103417&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the event of loss of the international recognition of a`
  line `National Sports Body, the normalisation process shall be implemented as per the International Charters`
  line `and Statutes and the Board shall not interfere in such process.`
  line
  line `(2) In the absence of the normalisation process referred to in sub-section (1) on the loss of`
  line `international recognition of a National Sports Body, or in the event of cancellation or suspension of Board`
  line `recognition of a National Sports Body under section 10, where the loss of recognition concern---`
  line
  line `(a) a National Olympic Committee or a National Paralympic Committee, the Board may constitute`
  line `an ad hoc administrative body in consultation with the International Olympic Committee or the`
  line `International Paralympic Committee, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) a National Sports Federation, the Board may, in consultation with the concerned International`
  line `Federation, wherever applicable, direct the National Olympic Committee to constitute an ad hoc`
  line `administrative body;`
  line
  line `(c) a Regional Sports Federation, the Board may in consultation with the concerned International`
  line `Federation, if any, constitute an ad hoc administrative body.`
  line
  line `(3) In the event of cancellation or suspension of Board recognition or registration of an affiliate unit of`
  line `a National Sports Body under section 10,---`
  line
  line `(a) where the cancellation or suspension of Board recognition or registration, concerns a State`
  line `sports federation, the Board may direct the concerned National Sports Federation or the Regional`
  line `Sports Federation; and`
  line
  line `(b) where the cancellation or suspension of Board recognition or registration, concerns a district`
  line `sports federation, the Board may direct the concerned State sports federation,`
  line
  line `to constitute an ad hoc administrative body consisting of such members as may be determined by the`
  line `Board in consultation with the National Sports Body or the concerned affiliate State unit, as the case may`
  line be.
  line
  line `(4) The ad hoc administrative body shall be responsible for administering the concerned sports body or`
  line `its affiliate units to ensure compliance with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The ad hoc administrative body referred to in sub-section (2) shall consist of a maximum of five`
  line `eminent sports administrators, who have previously held the office of a President or a Secretary General`
  line `or a Treasurer of a National Sports Body or who is or has served as a member of the Executive`
  line `Committee of the National Olympic Committee, having no past association with the sports discipline or`
  line `any conflict of interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be part of more than one ad hoc administrative body at the same time.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (103418)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Code of Ethics.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103418&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every National Sports Body shall formulate a Code of Ethics for the`
  line `members of its Executive Committee and other committees, employees, staff, sponsors, coaches, athletes,`
  line `officials, members, affiliates and such other relevant persons, in accordance with the guidelines specified`
  line `by the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Code of Ethics shall establish minimum standards for the ethical and appropriate conduct of`
  line `the persons specified in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The Code of Ethics shall be framed in accordance with the Code of Ethics of the International`
  line `Sports Bodies and in consonance with the applicable laws in India.`
  line
  line `(4) The Code of Ethics shall provide measures for protection of vulnerable persons against abuse by`
  line `person in a position of trust, responsibility or authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this sub-section, "person in a position of trust" means any person`
  line `who exercises authority, control or influence over another person, or a person on whom another person is`
  line `dependent and who is connected or associated with the affairs of the National Sports Body.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (103419)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Safe Sports Policy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103419&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall frame a comprehensive Safe Sports Policy applicable to`
  line `all activities, events, operations and proceedings conducted by the National Sports Bodies.`
  line
  line `(2) The Safe Sports Policy shall include provisions to ensure the protection and safety of women and`
  line `minor athletes and such other persons as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every National Sports Body shall establish an internal grievance redressal mechanism to address`
  line `the grievances raised by athletes, coaches and other individuals associated with such body, in a fair,`
  line `timely and transparent manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (103420)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Privileges of recognised sports organisation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103420&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Only a recognised sports organisation shall`
  line `be eligible to receive grants or any other financial assistance from the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) A recognised sports organisation, receiving grants or any other financial assistance from the`
  line `Central Government under sub-section (1) or from a State Government, shall be considered as a public`
  line `authority under the Right to Information Act, 2005 (22 of 2005), with respect to utilisation of such grants`
  line `or any other financial assistance.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (103421)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Duties of recognised sports organisation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103421&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `A recognised sports organisation shall ensure that all`
  line `its voting members and affiliate units, as applicable, complies with---`
  line
  line `(a) the International Charters and Statutes, as applicable, and shall exercise the rights, perform the`
  line `duties and discharge the functions as specified therein; and`
  line
  line `(b) the provisions of this Act and the rules and regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (103422)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `National Sports Election Panel and appointment of electoral officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103422&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government shall, on the recommendations of the Board, notify a National Sports Election Panel`
  line `consisting of such number of persons as it may deem necessary, who are retired Chief Election`
  line `Commissioner or Election Commissioner or Deputy Election Commissioner or retired State Election`
  line `Commissioner or Chief Electoral Officers of the States, with adequate experience of conduct of elections`
  line `under the Representation of the People Act, 1951 (43 of 1951).`
  line
  line `(2) The persons notified under sub-section (1) shall act as electoral officers to oversee the conduct`
  line `of free and fair elections to the Executive Committees and the Athletes Committee of the National`
  line `Sports Bodies.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall maintain a roster of the National Sports Election Panel in such manner as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The fees and other allowances to be paid to the persons notified under sub-section (1) shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The National Sports Bodies may appoint an electoral officer from the National Sports Election`
  line `Panel to oversee its election process and ensure free and fair elections:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Charters or Statutes of the International Sports Body require appointment`
  line `of any other person as an electoral officer, the concerned National Sports Body may appoint such other`
  line `person after furnishing the details, including qualifications and experience, of the person, to the Board.`
  line
  line `(6) Every National Sports Body, having affiliate units, shall prepare an Election Panel for the`
  line `conduct of free and fair elections of the Executive Committees of their affiliate units, consisting of`
  line `such number of retired persons as it may deem necessary, having adequate experience of conduct of`
  line `elections under the Representation of the People Act, 1951 (43 of 1951).`
  line
  line `(7) Every affiliate unit shall appoint an electoral officer from the roster to be maintained by the`
  line `National Sports Body, to oversee its election process and ensure free and fair elections.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (103423)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Constitution of National Sports Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103423&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by notification,`
  line `constitute a National Sports Tribunal consisting of a chairperson and two other members, to provide for`
  line `the independent, speedy, effective and cost-efficient disposal of sports related disputes.`
  line
  line `(2) The chairperson shall be a person who is or has been, a Judge of the Supreme Court or the Chief`
  line `Justice of a High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) The members shall be persons of eminence in public life with wide knowledge and experience`
  line `in sports, public administration and law.`
  line
  line `(4) The chairperson and the other members of the Tribunal shall be appointed by the Central`
  line `Government on the recommendations of a Search-cum-Selection Committee consisting of the`
  line `following members, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the Chief Justice of India or a Supreme Court Judge recommended by the Chief Justice of`
  line India---chairperson;
  line
  line `(b) the Secretary to the Government of India in the Ministry of Law and Justice---member;`
  line
  line `(c) the Secretary to the Government of India in the Department of Sports---member`
  line
  line `(5) The Search-cum-Selection Committee shall determine the procedure for making its`
  line recommendations.
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in any judgment, order or decree of any court, or in any`
  line `law for the time being in force, the Search-cum-Selection Committee shall recommend a panel of two`
  line `names for appointment to the post of chairperson or member, as the case may be, and the Central`
  line `Government shall take a decision on the recommendations made by that Committee, preferably within`
  line `three months from the date of such recommendation.`
  line
  line `(7) No appointment shall be invalid merely by reason of any vacancy or absence of a member in`
  line `the Search-cum-Selection Committee.`
  line
  line `(8) The term of office and other conditions of service of chairperson and members of the Tribunal`
  line `shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(9) The Tribunal shall formulate its own procedure for the conduct of its business including the`
  line `timelines to be followed for the disposal of matters.`
  line
  line `(10) All expenses incurred in connection with the Tribunal shall be defrayed out of the`
  line `Consolidated Fund of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (103424)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Removal of chairperson or members of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103424&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall remove`
  line `from office a chairperson or member of the Tribunal who---`
  line
  line `(a) has been adjudged an insolvent;`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government, involves`
  line `moral turpitude;`
  line
  line `(c) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as a member;`
  line
  line `(d) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as a`
  line `member; or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his position as to render his continuation in office prejudicial to public interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the chairperson or member is proposed to be removed on any ground specified`
  line `in clauses (c) to (e), he shall be informed of the charges against him and given an opportunity of being`
  line `heard in respect of those charges.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), a member of the Tribunal shall not be`
  line `removed from his office on the grounds specified therein unless the Chief Justice of India or his nominee`
  line `judge, on a reference being made to him in this behalf by the Central Government, has on inquiry held in`
  line `accordance with such procedure as he may specify in this behalf, recommended the removal.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (103425)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Staff of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103425&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, in consultation with the Tribunal, appoint`
  line `such officers and other employees as may be necessary for discharging the functions of the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) The officers and other employees of the Tribunal shall discharge their functions under the`
  line `general superintendence and control of the chairperson or any other member of the Tribunal to whom`
  line `powers for exercising such superintendence and control are delegated by the chairperson.`
  line
  line `(3) The qualifications, appointment, salary and allowances and other terms and conditions of`
  line `service of officers and other employees of the Tribunal shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (103426)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Exclusion of jurisdiction of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103426&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The Tribunal shall not have jurisdiction to adjudicate the`
  line `following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) any dispute, or conflict arising during the Olympic Games, Paralympic Games, Commonwealth`
  line `Games, Asian Games, or any other similar events organised by any International Federations;`
  line
  line `(b) any dispute falling within the exclusive jurisdiction of---`
  line
  line `(i) the internal disputes resolution committee of a National Sports Body; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any other tribunal or court; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any International Federation; or`
  line
  line `(iv) the Court of Arbitration for Sports established in Lausanne, Switzerland;`
  line
  line `(c) doping related disputes, where Disciplinary Panels constituted under the National Anti-Doping`
  line `Act, 2022 (15 of 2022) have exclusive jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(d) any matter in respect of which the International Charters and Statutes require the parties to`
  line `submit to specific mechanism or forum for adjudication.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (103427)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Members, etc., to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103427&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The members and other officers and employees of the`
  line `Board or the Tribunal shall be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of clause (28) of section 2`
  line `of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (103428)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Transfer of pending cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103428&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) All cases under civil jurisdiction falling within the scope of this`
  line `Act, in which the National Sports Bodies are impleaded as parties and are pending before a District Court`
  line `or High Court immediately before the constitution of the Tribunal, shall be transferred to the Tribunal on`
  line `and from such date as may be specified by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The cases transferred to the Tribunal under sub-section (1) may be heard and adjudicated from the`
  line `stage at which such dispute was pending in the concerned Court, or may be heard afresh if the Tribunal`
  line `deems appropriate after recording the reasons therefor in writing.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (103429)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Bar on jurisdiction of a civil court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103429&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any suit or`
  line `proceeding in respect of any matter on which the Tribunal is empowered under this Act to determine and`
  line `no injunction shall be granted by any court or other authority in respect of any action taken or to be taken`
  line `in pursuance of any power conferred on the Tribunal by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (103430)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Powers of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103430&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tribunal shall have, for the purposes of discharging its functions`
  line `under this Act, the same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908) while trying a suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) calling for any public record or document or a copy of such record or document, from any`
  line `office, subject to the provisions of sections 129 and 130 of the Bharatiya Sakshya Adhiniyam, 2023`
  line `(47 of 2023);`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(f) reviewing its decisions;`
  line
  line `(g) dismissing an application for default or deciding it, ex parte;`
  line
  line `(h) setting aside any order of dismissal of any application for default or any order passed by it,`
  line `ex parte; and`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every proceeding before the Tribunal shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of sections 228, 229, 233, 257 and 267 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023).`
  line
  line `(3) The Tribunal shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purpose of section 215 of the Bharatiya`
  line `Nagarik Suraksha Sanhita, 2023 (46 of 2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (103431)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Appeal to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103431&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Unless the International Charters and Statutes provide for appeal`
  line `before the Court of Arbitration for Sport, an appeal shall lie against any order of the Tribunal, not being`
  line `an interlocutory order, to the Supreme Court.`
  line
  line `(2) No appeal shall lie against any decision made by the Tribunal with the consent of the parties.`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under this section shall be preferred within a period of thirty days from the date of the`
  line `decision appealed against:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Supreme Court may entertain the appeal after the expiry of the said period of thirty`
  line `days, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from preferring the appeal in`
  line time.
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (103432)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Orders passed by Tribunal to be executable as a decree.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103432&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) An order passed by the Tribunal`
  line `under this Act shall be executable as a decree of a civil court, and for this purpose, the Tribunal shall have`
  line `all the powers of a civil court.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Tribunal may transmit any order made`
  line `by it to a civil court having local jurisdiction and such civil court shall execute the order as if it were a`
  line `decree made by that court.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (103433)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Use of national names and insignia.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103433&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any sports organisation desirous of using the word`
  line `"India" or "Indian" or "National" or any national insignia or symbols in any language in its registered`
  line `name, operating name, logo or otherwise in its affairs, shall obtain a no-objection certificate from the`
  line `Central Government for such use:`
  line
  line `Provided that a sports organisation other than a recognised sports organisation shall, in addition to the`
  line `requirements under this sub-section, obtain written consent of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) No sports organisation shall use the name "India" or the name of any State or district in India, or`
  line `conduct any sports trials, tournaments, or events upon the suspension or cancellation of its recognition by`
  line `the Board under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) No person or group of persons, either individually or collectively, shall represent or be allowed to`
  line `represent India or any State or district in India, in any sports trials, tournaments or events of designated`
  line `sports without an authorisation by a National Sports Body or its affiliate unit.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (103434)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title Fund.
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103434&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a Fund to be called the National Sports Board Fund and`
  line `there shall be credited thereto---`
  line
  line `(a) all grants, fees and charges received by the Board under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(b) all sums received by the Board from such other sources as may be decided upon by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) The Fund constituted under sub-section (1) shall be applied for meeting---`
  line
  line `(a) the salaries and allowances payable to the Chairperson and Members of the Board and the`
  line `administrative expenses including the salaries and allowances payable to or in respect of officers and`
  line `other employees of the Board; and`
  line
  line `(b) all other expenses for meeting the objects and for the purposes authorised by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (103435)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103435&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant records`
  line `and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Board shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Board to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any other person appointed by him in`
  line `connection with the audit of the accounts of the Board shall have the same rights and privileges and`
  line `authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India generally has, in`
  line `connection with the audit of the Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand`
  line `the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect`
  line `any of the offices of the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Board as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (103436)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Measures for promotion and development of sports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103436&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government in`
  line `consonance with the International Charters and Statutes, may take such measures as may be prescribed, as`
  line `it considers necessary for the promotion and development of sports, including in the public interest.`
  line
  line `(2) The measures referred to in sub-section (1), may include,---`
  line
  line `(a) the guiding principles for the conduct of elections by the National Sports Bodies, including`
  line `model election rules;`
  line
  line `(b) the promotion of the welfare and interests of sportspersons;`
  line
  line `(c) the protection of the data and privacy of sportspersons; and`
  line
  line `(d) the appropriate use of technology and analytics in the context of sport.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (103437)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103437&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules for carrying`
  line `out the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government, while making rules under this section, shall take into`
  line `consideration the International Charters and Statutes, with the objective of ensuring transparency,`
  line `accountability, and integrity in the management and administration of sports in India.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the relevant affiliations of Regional Sports Federation under sub-section (6) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the sportspersons of outstanding merit and other categories of persons under the proviso to`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) the mode of election to different bodies, committees and offices including their term, eligibility`
  line `criteria and disqualification of members thereof, and other matters of governance under sub-section (4)`
  line `of section 4;`
  line
  line `(d) the composition and number of Members of the Board under sub-section (1) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(e) the composition of the search-cum-selection committee under sub-section (2) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(f) the salary and allowances, term of office of Chairperson and other Members of the Board and`
  line `other terms and conditions of their service including removal from service, under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 5;`
  line
  line `(g) other places in which the Board shall establish its branch offices under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 5;`
  line
  line `(h) the measures to be taken by the Board for ensuring protection of the rights and welfare of`
  line `athletes and support personnel under clause (i) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(i) other powers and functions of the Board under clause (j) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(j) the qualifications, appointment, salary and allowances and other terms and conditions of service`
  line `of the officers and the other employees of the Board under sub-section (3) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(k) the conditions and the manner in which affiliate units of the National Sports Bodies shall ensure`
  line `registration of their affiliate units with the Board under sub-section (6) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(l) other persons to be covered by the Safe Sports Policy under sub-section (2) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(m) manner of maintaining roster of the National Sports Election Panel by the Board under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(n) the fees and other allowances to be paid to the empanelled persons under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 16;`
  line
  line `(o) the term of office and other conditions of service of chairperson and members of Tribunal under`
  line `sub-section (8) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(p) the qualifications, appointment, salary and allowances and other terms and conditions of service`
  line `of the officers and the other employees of the Tribunal under sub-section (3) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(q) any other matter under clause (i) of sub-section (1) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(r) the form in which the Board shall prepare annual statement of accounts under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 29;`
  line
  line `(s) the measures to be taken by the Central Government for the promotion and development of`
  line `sports under sub-section (1) of section 30; and`
  line
  line `(t) any other matter which is to be, or may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (103438)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103438&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government, by notification, make regulations consistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder, to`
  line `carry out the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board, while making regulations under this section, shall comply with the`
  line `International Charters and Statutes, with the objective of ensuring transparency, accountability, and`
  line `integrity in the management and administration of sports in India.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `make provision for---`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of maintaining register of the National Sports Bodies and their respective affiliate`
  line `units by the Board under clause (b) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) the form, manner and particulars of application under sub-section (2) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(c) other criteria and conditions to be complied by the sports organisations under clause (d) of`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(d) the intervals and procedure for renewal of Board recognition under sub-section (4) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(e) the eligibility criteria for Board recognition of the sports organisation as a National Sports`
  line `Promotion Organisation, the manner of their governance and functioning and the intervals and`
  line `procedure for renewal of such recognition under sub-section (8) of section 8; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which is to be, or may be, specified by regulations under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (103439)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Laying of rules, regulations and notifications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103439&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Every rule, regulation and every notification`
  line `made or issued under this Act shall be laid as soon as may be, after it is made or issued, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days, which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule, regulation or notification or both Houses agree that the rule, regulation or notification should`
  line `not be made or issued, the rule, regulation or notification shall thereafter have effect only in such`
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule,`
  line `regulation or notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (103440)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power to exempt in special cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103440&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government considers it necessary and`
  line `expedient so to do in the public interest for the promotion of specific sport disciplines consistent with the`
  line `spirit of good governance enshrined in the Olympic Charter, it may, in consultation with the Board and`
  line `the concerned International Sports Body, by notification, direct that subject to such conditions and`
  line `restrictions, if any, and for such period as may be specified in the notification, all or any of the provisions`
  line `of this Act or any rule or regulation made thereunder shall not apply to a National Sports Body or its`
  line `affiliate unit specified therein.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification, and for reasons to be recorded in writing, relax the`
  line `eligibility criteria for the members of the Executive Committee, if such person is serving in the executive`
  line `committee or a similar body of a corresponding International Sports Body or is in the General Body of the`
  line `International Olympic Committee or International Paralympic Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (103441)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power to issue directions and impose restrictions in national interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103441&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, from time to time, give such directions as it may think fit, to the Board or any other`
  line `person or entity for the efficient administration of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by an order, impose reasonable restrictions on the participation of`
  line `any national team of a concerned sport in international sports competitions or participation of any`
  line `individual in the activities of the national sports, under extraordinary circumstances and in the interest of`
  line `national security, public order and safety.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (103442)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103442&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against any Member of the Board or member of a National Sports Body or the Tribunal or any officer`
  line `or other employee of such authorities or any other person or authority for anything which has been done`
  line `or is intended to be done in good faith under this Act or the rules and regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (103443)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Conflicts with International Charters and Statutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103443&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Sports Bodies shall`
  line `primarily be guided by the International Charters and Statutes in the governance of its affairs.`
  line
  line `(2) In the event of any conflict between a provision of this Act and the International Charters and`
  line `Statutes, the Central Government may, after consulting the Board and the concerned International Sports`
  line `Body as may be deemed necessary, issue a clarificatory notification in this regard.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (103444)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397&sectionId=103444&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_34_92_00002_2025-25_1767697307397
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to any provision of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to it to be necessary, for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of five years from`
  line `the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
